body:
> Regarding the attributes that are not working, is there any way we can remove them from the UI as options? (I'm guessing this would be possibly trickier than getting them to work but just have to ask.)

=> We may disable those attributes setting if it doesn't work.

Ref: https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/pull/2451#issuecomment-401822905

comment_data.body:
@pq, I already double check this problem.
But it looks hard to decide.
Reason:
There is only one attribute doesn't work well.
That attribute is `Effect`.

There are some `Effect` like `Dotted line `, `Underwaved` some of them work, and some doesn't work well. (See: https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/pull/2451)

So I don't know what should we do next :|,
Thanks for following up.  Am I right that some effects DO work as expected and it's just that some don't work as well?

Yes, you right.
Effect type is work.
But Effect color doesn't work.
For example:
Effect `Bold underscored` -> bold + underscored WORKED. Color effect doesn't work.
Also, there is setting `strip mark color`. That setting seems related to this issue: https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/issues/2458

Great.  If it's common that folks try a color effect (though I expect it won't be) we can explore further or add a popup warning them that the setting won't have any effect.

Besides that, I think we can close this as done?
